# Tenar (Arha) · the Eaten One

a persona of the U1 (Le Guin) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** A girl of Atuan made Arha, the Eaten One, priestess of the Tombs — who reclaimed the name Tenar and lived on as Goha, widow and mother.

**what —** The heart of *The Tombs of Atuan* and *Tehanu* — the keeper of the dark who chose the light, and whose later life Le Guin makes the equal of any wizard's.

**where —** The Tombs of Atuan and the Undertomb's labyrinth, then the farms of Middle Valley and Re Albi on Gont.

**why —** Because a name taken in the dark can be given back; because freedom costs more than power; because an ordinary life, fully chosen, is its own great work.

**how —** By keeping the Ring in the dark, by trusting Ged enough to leave her whole world behind, and by daring to choose for herself when no one had ever let her choose.

**◌ the arc —** From a child consumed by the nameless Powers to a woman who names herself, raises a scarred child, and meets dragons as kin; Le Guin's recovery of the domestic and the feminine as heroic.

**the seal —** They ate my name in the dark; in the dark a man gave it back — and I walked out into the light by my own choosing.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Ursula K. Le Guin's fiction, personified as a U1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © the Ursula K. Le Guin estate; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

